    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MAMARONECK: INJUNCTION GRANTED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ROBERT WORTH</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Worth, Robert</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York State Supreme Court grants preliminary injunction barring village of Mamaroneck from awarding contract to Sportime for sports complex at Harbor Island Park; upholds right of first refusal to current operator of tennis courts, Harbor View Racquet Club (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The State Supreme Court in White Plains has granted a preliminary injunction barring the village of Mamaroneck from giving a contract to a Long Island developer, Sportime, for a sports complex at Harbor Island Park. The current operator of the tennis courts in the park, Harbor View Racquet Club, had a right of first refusal, which the court upheld. The village had argued that Harbor View lacked the money and expertise to build the new facility. ''We're looking into an appeal,'' Steven Silveberg, the village attorney, said.</p>
        <p>ROBERT WORTH</p>
      </block>
